---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Stephen Stanwood — stanwood.dev"
  description="Builder and designer in Campbell, California. Makes apps, games, and tools that solve small everyday problems or just look cool. Shipping fast and keeping it fun."
  slug="about"
  themeColor="#fffef5"
  fontsUrl="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Mono:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Cabin:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Permanent+Marker&display=swap"
  schemaType="WebSite"
  schemaName="Stephen Stanwood"
>
  <style is:global>
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    :root {
      --bg: #fffef5;
      --ink: #111;
      --yellow: #f5e642;
      --orange: #ff5c1a;
      --blue: #1a4fff;
      --pixel: 3px;
    }

    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }

    body {
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--ink);
      font-family: 'Cabin', sans-serif;
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      overflow-x: hidden;
    }

    .about-wrap {
      max-width: 640px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 48px 24px 80px;
    }

    .about-header {
      background: var(--yellow);
      border: var(--pixel) solid var(--ink);
      box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--ink);
      padding: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    .about-header h1 {
      font-family: 'Permanent Marker', cursive;
      font-size: 36px;
      line-height: 1.2;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .about-header .subtitle {
      font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 13px;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      opacity: 0.7;
    }

    .about-section {
      margin-bottom: 36px;
    }

    .about-section h2 {
      font-family: 'Permanent Marker', cursive;
      font-size: 22px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      border-bottom: var(--pixel) solid var(--ink);
      padding-bottom: 6px;
      display: inline-block;
    }

    .about-section p {
      margin-bottom: 14px;
    }

    .about-section a {
      color: var(--blue);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-underline-offset: 2px;
    }

    .about-section a:hover {
      color: var(--orange);
    }

    .project-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
    }

    .project-list li {
      border: 2px solid var(--ink);
      padding: 12px 16px;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      background: #fff;
      box-shadow: 3px 3px 0 var(--ink);
    }

    .project-list li a {
      font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: var(--ink);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .project-list li a:hover {
      color: var(--blue);
    }

    .project-list li .tag {
      font-size: 13px;
      opacity: 0.6;
      margin-left: 8px;
    }

    .back-link {
      display: inline-block;
      font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 13px;
      color: var(--ink);
      text-decoration: none;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
      opacity: 0.6;
    }

    .back-link:hover {
      opacity: 1;
    }

    .connect-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    .connect-list li {
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    .connect-list a {
      color: var(--ink);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .connect-list a:hover {
      color: var(--orange);
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .about-header h1 { font-size: 28px; }
      .about-wrap { padding: 32px 16px 60px; }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="about-wrap">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; stanwood.dev</a>

    <div class="about-header">
      <h1>Stephen Stanwood</h1>
      <div class="subtitle">builder &middot; designer &middot; developer &middot; campbell, ca</div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>Who I Am</h2>
      <p>
        I'm Stephen Stanwood, a builder and designer based in Campbell, California (just south of San Jose).
        I make apps, games, and tools that make life a little simpler or a little more fun.
        Everything on <a href="/">stanwood.dev</a> is something I built because I wanted it to exist.
      </p>
      <p>
        I studied public policy at the University of Chicago and law and business at Georgetown and Santa Clara.
        I've worked at a small law firm, ran my own practice for a while, and also spent time with organizations like City Year and the Electronic Frontier Foundation.
        These days you'll mostly find me swimming pre-dawn laps with a wonderful team, building here, doing yoga, and chasing my two-year-old daughter around the house.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>What I Build</h2>
      <p>
        Tools for curious people — useful, fun, or both, and small enough to actually finish.
        Everything here is free to use. Here's the full list:
      </p>
      <ul class="project-list">
        <li><a href="https://nbanow.app">NBA Now</a> <span class="tag">best NBA game to watch right now</span></li>
        <li><a href="/wtwtw">What to Watch This Week</a> <span class="tag">best game each night across MLB, NBA &amp; NHL</span></li>
        <li><a href="/mlb-gamerank">MLB GameRank</a> <span class="tag">best MLB game to watch right now</span></li>
        <li><a href="/show-swipe">Show Swipe</a> <span class="tag">swipe through movie &amp; TV trailers</span></li>
        <li><a href="/swim">Lap Lab</a> <span class="tag">custom swim workouts</span></li>
        <li><a href="/nearest-coffee">Nearest Coffee</a> <span class="tag">nearest open coffee shop</span></li>
        <li><a href="/radar">AI Radar</a> <span class="tag">curated AI launches for builders</span></li>
        <li><a href="/which-model">Which Model?</a> <span class="tag">pick the right AI model for your task</span></li>
        <li><a href="/tldr">TL;DR</a> <span class="tag">drop a PDF, get the short version</span></li>
        <li><a href="/redesign-rolodex">Redesign Rolodex</a> <span class="tag">alternate-universe redesigns for any website</span></li>
        <li><a href="/green-light">Green Light</a> <span class="tag">taste quiz → know what to order</span></li>
        <li><a href="/ship-clock">Ship Clock</a> <span class="tag">days since your last deploy</span></li>
        <li><a href="/campbell">Campbell, CA</a> <span class="tag">city services, events &amp; permits in one place</span></li>
        <li><a href="/driverless">Driverless Cars</a> <span class="tag">self-driving, by the numbers</span></li>
        <li><a href="/museum-label">Museum Label</a> <span class="tag">deadpan museum placard for any object</span></li>
        <li><a href="/pixel-aquarium">Pixel Aquarium</a> <span class="tag">click to feed the fish</span></li>
        <li><a href="/pixel-tide">Pixel Tide</a> <span class="tag">no winning, just vibes</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>How I Build</h2>
      <p>
        Most of what you see here is built with <strong>Astro 5</strong>, <strong>React</strong>, and <strong>Tailwind v4</strong>, deployed on <strong>Vercel</strong>.
        APIs I lean on most: Claude (Anthropic) for AI features, Google Places for location tools, and ESPN for live sports data.
      </p>
      <p>
        I build fast and iterate — ship something that works, then refine. Most projects go from idea to live in a day or two.
        I use <a href="https://claude.ai/claude-code">Claude Code</a> for the heavy lifting and love seeing how far that gets me before I have to think hard.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-section">
      <h2>Connect</h2>
      <ul class="connect-list">
        <li>&rarr; <a href="mailto:stephen@stanwood.dev">stephen@stanwood.dev</a></li>
        <li>&rarr; <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/stephenstanwood">LinkedIn</a></li>
        <li>&rarr; <a href="https://github.com/stephenstanwood">GitHub</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
